properties.headline: COVID-19 Border Control - TIBOOBURRA Fortville Gate Road at Queensland border
properties.otherAdvice:

Any person that has been in a declared COVID-19 hotspot during the past 14 days must not enter Queensland. From 1am Thursday 1 October, the NSW border zone has been extended; see the Queensland government website for more information.

Anyone attempting to enter Queensland from NSW must complete a Queensland Border Declaration Pass.

  • This border control point is accessible via a coded lock.
  • Declaration pass holders must call Thargomindah Police Station on 07 4655 3200 between 8am and 5pm for the code to gate.
  • Pass holders should call in advance due to a lack of suitable reception at the border control point.

properties.headline: CHANGED TRAFFIC CONDITIONS - Royal National Park - Saturday 3 to Monday 5 October - ROYAL NATIONAL PARK Princes Hwy at McKell Ave and Farnell Ave
properties.otherAdvice:
The Royal National Park is expected to be busy over the October long weekend period from Saturday 3 to Monday 5 October. Road closures will be in place as precincts and car parks reach capacity including Wattamolla Beach, Garie Beach, Audley, Maianbar and Bundeena.

Note that Sir Bertram Stevens Dr is currently closed between Bundeena Dr and Wises Track see roadworks details and detour map. Use the Farnell Ave, Loftus park entry for access to Audley Weir. Use the McKell Ave, Waterfall park entry for access to Wattamolla, Bundeena, Maianbar and Garie Beach. 

When parking capacity is reached across all precincts, traffic will only be permitted to travel through the park. If there are significant delays, both the northern and southern entries to the park via Farnell Ave in Loftus and via Lady Wakehurst Dr in Otford will close. Entry will be maintained via McKell Ave in Waterfall for residents only. 

Visitors are encouraged to check the Royal National Park local alerts before travelling for updates on precinct access.

Road closures when precincts reach capacity:

- Wattamolla Rd between Sir Bertram Stevens Dr and Wattamolla Beach - CLOSED

- Garie Rd between Sir Bertram Stevens Dr and Garie Beach - CLOSED

- Maianbar Rd between Bundeena Dr and Maianbar township

- Bundeena Dr between Sir Bertram Stevens Dr and Bundeena township

Traffic controllers and NSW Police will be on site managing access for local residents on Maianbar Rd and Bundeena Dr upon proof of residential address.
